{
  "texts": [
    "This innovative and promising business model has quickly become common practice, benefiting both service providers and customers [11,36].",
    "Specifically, LLM service providers can generate profits to cover the costs of training LLMs, while customers can efficiently deploy powerful LLMs without the need for advanced AI infrastructure.In this work, we assume the existence of a pretrained LLM as an external service and explore how to utilize this system to improve traditional sequential recommender systems in a privacy-preserving manner.",
    "Specifically, we conduct experiments with the most representative LLMs including both discriminative LLMs (e.g., BERT and Longformer) and advanced generative LLMs (Llama2 and Llama3).",
    "In this section, we present the basic background knowledge of federated sequential recommender systems and the base sequential recommendation models used in our work.",
    "The notations used in this paper are under the following rules: the bold lowercases (e.g., a) are vectors, the bold uppercases (e.g., A) represent matrices or models, and the squiggle uppercase (e.g., A) denotes sets or functions."
  ]
}